Ad Text:
Business Analyst
Surry Hills
5-month initial contract
Hybrid working

We’re looking for an experienced Business Analyst to join Technology, Data & Digital and support a high-impact Editorial Technology RFI/RFP. This role sits at the centre of a strategic initiative, translating complex business needs into clear requirements that directly shape vendor selection and future platform direction.

You’ll partner with senior stakeholders, document current and future-state processes, and develop evaluation criteria that influence major technology decisions. It’s a focused, high-impact contract for a commercially savvy BA who enjoys stakeholder engagement and driving meaningful outcomes.

What’s the role?
 
Lead business analysis activities for a high-profile Editorial Technology RFI/RFP, from requirements definition through to vendor evaluation.
Translate complex business and operational needs into clear, structured requirements that inform procurement and platform decisions.
Document current-state and future-state processes, including as-is and to-be workflows, to support solution design and selection.
Partner closely with senior business, technical stakeholders, and vendors to clarify requirements and respond to RFP queries.

Who are you?
 
An experienced Business Analyst with a strong track record delivering RFI/RFPs and supporting vendor selection for technology initiatives.
A critical thinker with excellent analytical skills, able to distil complex problems into clear, actionable requirements.
A confident communicator who can engage effectively with senior stakeholders, technical teams, and external vendors.
Strong in business process design and documentation, including as-is / to-be mapping across digital and technology environments.
Commercially astute, detail-oriented, and comfortable operating in fast-paced, cross-functional project teams.

Who are we?
We’re part of News Corp Australia, one of the country’s most influential media organisations, trusted by more than 18 million Australians each month. Our technology teams power a diverse portfolio of digital products across publishing, subscriptions, and consumer platforms, operating at significant scale and complexity.

We value technical excellence, clarity of thinking, and strong collaboration between product and engineering. Joining us means working on meaningful, high-impact systems within a mature, evolving technology environment where your technical judgement genuinely matters.

What’s next?
Apply now or for more information on careers at News Corp Australia visit
www.newscorpaustralia.com/careers

Diversity strengthens our national teams and newsroom as we seek to tell stories that represent the communities of Australia. Our people make us unique, and we are committed to equal employment opportunities regardless of race, religion, sexual orientation, age, disability, or gender identity. Applicants of diverse backgrounds are encouraged to apply.

We are committed to ensuring an accessible and supportive recruitment process. If you require adjustments or accommodations at any stage, please let us know. For more information on Diversity at News Corp Australia, visit www.newscorpaustralia.com/careers under the Diversity@News section.

This role sits at the intersection of market analysis, pricing, forecasting and broader development activities, providing insights that directly inform commercial decision-making and strategy.
You’ll work closely with cross-functional teams analysing spot and forward market behaviour, external curves from an in-house lens.

Key Responsibilities
Model and analyse NEM market trends, pricing dynamics and forward curves
Develop and maintain analytical tools using SQL and Python to support forecasting and market views
Produce clear insights from quantitative analysis to inform development, pricing and commercial strategy
Analyse spot market outcomes and external data to support internal market positions and assumptions
Prepare reporting and commentary on market trends from an in-house analytical perspective
Collaborate closely with trading, commercial and development teams across the business
Qualifications
Experience in the NEM, either as an energy market analyst or spot trader is essential
Strong capability in SQL and Python (required)
Experience with the WEM and international NZ and APAC energy markets is highhly regarded
Solid understanding of spot and forward electricity markets, pricing and forecasting
Ability to translate complex analysis into clear commercial insights
Degree in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, engineering, mathematics or similar
Benefits
Senior analytical role with direct exposure to market-facing decision-making 
Strong pipeline of projects across APAC
Flexible working arrangements and supportive, high-calibre leadership
Competitive remuneration package and attractive bonus
If this sounds like you, apply now or send your CV directly to debora.lengler@acrworld.com for a confidential discussion.

Sydney | Hybrid (3 days on-site, 2 WFH) | 12 Month Contract

This role focuses on delivery orchestration and senior stakeholder engagement, ensuring data governance, platform and reporting initiatives come together to deliver trusted, adoption-ready data assets that support real business decisions.

The initial focus will be on the Student and Operations data domains, working closely with business leaders and specialist delivery teams.

Partner with senior stakeholders to clarify business problems, decisions, KPIs and reporting needs.

Facilitate prioritisation and trade-off decisions where demand exceeds capacity.
Provide transparent reporting on progress, risks and dependencies.
Support transition of delivered outcomes into business-as-usual ownership.
About You

Proven experience leading complex, cross-functional delivery in large or regulated environments.
Strong stakeholder engagement skills across technical and non-technical audiences.
Experience delivering data, analytics or reporting initiatives.
Ability to translate complexity into clear plans, actions and outcomes.
Comfortable operating in federated or matrixed delivery models.
Delivery-focused, pragmatic and outcome-oriented.
Highly Desirable

Experience working with data domains or data products.
Familiarity with data governance enabled delivery models.
Experience in education, government or similarly complex environments.
Contract Details

12 month day rate contract (rate to be confirmed)
Sydney
Hybrid working: 3 days on-site, 2 days from home

Influence risk insights across a large financial services group
Hybrid working with strong flexibility and wellbeing support
Career development within a growing internal analytics capability

Use data and analytics to strengthen risk oversight and deliver insights that support better decisions across Suncorp, while advancing your data analytics career.

About the Role

As an Analytics Manager in Internal Audit, you will apply advanced data analytics techniques to support effective risk oversight and assurance activities. Working closely with audit, risk, and technology teams, you will deliver end to end analytics engagements that generate clear, actionable insights. This role offers broad exposure across the Suncorp Group and the opportunity to contribute to the growth of our internal audit analytics capability.

What You’ll Do

Deliver multiple analytics engagements that provide evidence-based insights into the effectiveness of risk management processes across the organisation
Partner with Internal Audit and business stakeholders to define analytics scopes, design testing approaches, and address key risk questions
Manage the full analytics lifecycle, including data acquisition, preparation, analysis, documentation, and communication of findings
Translate complex analytical outcomes into clear, meaningful insights using data visualisation and concise narrative for both technical and non-technical audiences
Contribute to continuous improvement by sharing knowledge, supporting training initiatives, and participating in quality assurance and peer reviews

What You’ll Bring

Significant experience in analytics or data-centric roles, applying analytical techniques to solve complex business or risk problems
Strong hands-on experience with SQL-based tools, such as SQL Server or AWS Redshift, to extract and analyse large datasets
Experience across the end to end analytics process, from problem definition through to insight communication and stakeholder engagement
Familiarity with data visualisation tools such as Tableau or Power BI, with a focus on producing clear and impactful insights
Experience using Python will be highly regarded
Ability to work autonomously while also collaborating effectively with audit, risk, and technology professionals

What You’ll Enjoy

Access our award-winning Shine platform – your central hub for exclusive perks, wellbeing support, career development, and recognition. Shine has been recognised for excellence in employee experience, making it easier than ever to access what matters most to you.

Hybrid working, flexible leave, 20 weeks paid parental leave, and up to 5 days paid flexible leave annually
Paid study support, career breaks, on-the-job learning, and a $1,000 referral bonus for eligible employees
Free wellbeing coaching, a dedicated Employee Council, and confidential EAP access
Discounts at 400+ retailers, insurance savings, gym memberships, and reduced super fees
Paid volunteer leave, donation matching, and unlimited emergency response leave
Performance-based bonuses and Suncorp shares for eligible employees
Diversity is celebrated through employee resource groups and inclusive policies for all families

Explore our full benefits: www.suncorpgroup.com.au/careers/benefits

At Suncorp we believe we are our best when our workforce is as diverse, talented and passionate as the communities in which we live and operate, and where our people feel included, valued and connected. We are passionate about inspiring our people by creating a diverse, accessible, and inclusive culture, offering flexible work, career development and internal mobility, and building connected relationships amongst our team members and with our customers.

Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
At ASIC, you can be the change that ensures a fair, strong and efficient financial system for the benefit of all Australians. Contribute to delivering on ASIC's purpose, vision, and strategic priorities to help maintain the integrity of the financial system and protect consumers from harm.

 

The Australian Government has announced the stabilisation of existing business registers and their transfer from the Australian Taxation Office (ATO) back to ASIC, under the Registry Connect (RC) Program. This program aims to deliver reliable, secure, trusted, and efficient registry services to support the economy for the benefit of all Australians.

Sydney or Melbourne locations
24 month fixed term contract
Salary from $152,074 to $163,970 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications will close at 11:59pm AEDT, Monday 9 February 2026 

 

The team 

The Digital, Data & Technology (DD&T) Portfolio Office delivers a broad suite of services in portfolio management, project delivery, business planning, and governance to support ASIC's strategic priorities. We work in close partnership with ASIC IT and the newly established RegistryConnect (RC) program to ensure projects are aligned with both strategic direction and operational needs.

 

The role

The Senior Data Business Analyst will play a lead role in the delivery of actionable insights by transforming raw data into meaningful information using tools like Power BI. Operating within ASIC's RegistryConnect Program, the role supports strategic decision-making, drives stakeholder engagement, and ensures alignment between business needs and technical solutions.

 

More specifically, you will: 

Lead Data Business Analysis practices at ASIC by applying established frameworks and supporting team delivery of project outcomes.
Champion the Data Business Analysis function and contribute to project success by aligning efforts with business objectives.
Collaborate with ASIC Registry Business, IT stakeholders, and the CDAO to elicit and document business data requirements.
Identify opportunities to enhance Data BA processes and promote innovation through effective stakeholder engagement.
Communicate business requirements clearly to data professionals, including Data Modellers, Architects, and Engineers.
Define and document data governance requirements, providing support throughout the project lifecycle, including Privacy Impact Assessments (PIAs).

 

About you

The ideal candidate for this role is a strategic and experienced data professional with significant experience in leading the delivery of actionable insights to support business decision-making. They will bring with them deep expertise in areas such as Data Business Analysis, championing innovation and ensure alignment between data initiatives and organisational goals.

As a confident communicator and trusted advisor, they will also demonstrate a proven ability to foster collaboration across business and technical teams to drive meaningful outcomes.

 

 

In addition, you will have:

Bachelor's degree or higher in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related discipline.
Strong ability to analyse business challenges, identify opportunities, and document clear, actionable requirements.
Proficient in developing user stories and acceptance criteria within DevOps environments.
Proven experience building and maintaining effective stakeholder relationships to drive outcomes.
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to translate technical concepts for non-technical audiences.
Extensive experience in data analysis and profiling using structured query languages (SQL).
Deep expertise in Databricks and Data Lake technologies.
Solid understanding of data modelling principles, including Data Vault 2.0 methodology.
Experienced in collaborating with Data Governance teams and understanding their compliance obligations.
Significant knowledge of data management principles and the full data lifecycle.

 

Click ‘apply' to start your application. Applications will close at 11:59pm AEDT, Monday 9 February 2026.

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms. 

ASIC is an equal opportunity employer seeking people who want to make a difference. ASIC is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Applications from people of all ages, cultural backgrounds, abilities, LGBTIQ+ identity, and people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander decent are encouraged to apply. 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation

Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development

Click here to view ASIC's salary and benefits guide.

To read more about ASIC, you can visit our website or review our Corporate Plan.

To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.

Job Title: Senior Manager, ESG and Emissions Reporting
Ad Text:
Global ASX 50 listed market leader in sustainability, supply chain and logistics

Lead global ESG and emissions reporting in a fast‑evolving regulatory environment

Inclusive and supportive culture | Flexible/hybrid work environment

About the Job

Are you passionate about sustainability, data integrity and high‑quality reporting? Do you thrive in complex, fast‑moving environments where your expertise directly shapes how a global business measures and communicates its environmental impact?

This is a newly created senior role within Brambles' ESG Global Finance team, responsible for the integrity, accuracy and timely delivery of the Group's emissions and ESG reporting. With an initial focus on carbon emissions, the role plays a critical part in ensuring Brambles continues to meet current and emerging ESG regulatory and assurance requirements globally, while maintaining its position as a sustainability leader.

Reporting to the ESG Global Finance Lead, you will take a hands‑on leadership approach to emissions reporting, data quality and process improvement. You will work closely with stakeholders across Finance, Sustainability, Supply Chain, Technology Services, HR and regional teams to source, analyse, challenge and explain data, and to embed financial‑grade rigour into ESG reporting processes.

You will lead the preparation of key external disclosures, including emissions reporting within the Annual Report, the AASB‑compliant Climate Report, and European CSRD deliverables, and support assurance activities and Board‑level reporting. This role is based in Sydney CBD with flexible hybrid work arrangements.

Key responsibilities include:

Lead the preparation and review of global emissions reporting for internal, statutory and external disclosures

Coordinate quarterly emissions data collection, review and consolidation across regions

Own data quality, controls, documentation and continuous improvement for emissions metrics

Manage and support the emissions assurance process, liaising with external assurance providers

Partner with cross‑functional teams (Supply Chain, Sustainability, TS, Finance) to ensure robust, timely and accurate data

Analyse emissions performance and translate outcomes into clear insights for senior leaders

Support broader ESG and sustainability reporting, surveys and indices (e.g. CDP, DJSI)

Stay across evolving standards and methodologies (e.g. GHG Protocol, GLEC, AASB S1/S2, CSRD) and ensure ongoing compliance

Lead and develop team members while acting as a trusted subject‑matter expert across the business

What will ensure your success:

Deep expertise in carbon accounting and emissions reporting, ideally within a global or ASX‑listed organisation

Strong experience applying recognised frameworks such as the GHG Protocol, ISO standards or GLEC

Proven ability to work hands‑on with complex datasets, systems and detailed calculations

Experience delivering assured, externally reported metrics under tight regulatory timeframes

Highly developed stakeholder management skills, with the confidence to engage senior leaders

Strong analytical, problem‑solving and communication skills, with a keen eye for detail

A collaborative, practical and resilient approach in a fast‑evolving regulatory environment

Big 4 audit experience strongly preferred as part of solid post-qualification experience alongside commercial experience in ASX-listed reporting

If you're looking for a challenging and rewarding opportunity with an innovative company where you are empowered to make a difference, we want to hear from you!

About Brambles

Brambles Limited (ASX: BXB) Brambles is a global provider of logistics solutions, connecting the world's supply network through its operations, people and technology.

Brambles operates across 60 countries primarily through its CHEP brand, harnessing its industry-leading expertise and the unmatched scale of its asset pool of 347 million pallets, crates and containers through a network of 750+ service centres.

Through its regenerative ambition, built on decades of leadership in the circular economy, Brambles has become one of the world's most sustainable companies.

Since its origin in 1875, Brambles has been at the forefront of innovation. Today, it continues to invest in the future, bringing enhanced connections, visibility and foresight, developing solutions to unlock new value and make the world's supply network more resilient and regenerative.

Brambles is listed on the Australian Securities Exchange and an ASX50 constituent. The Group employs approximately 13,000 people, with its largest operations in North America and Europe.

Brambles is an accredited Top Employer and offers a range of employee benefits including a competitive salary, bonus opportunities, a supportive learning and development culture and a wide range of opportunities to assist you in achieving your career aspirations. Brambles provides you unparalleled opportunities to advance and accelerate your career and is large enough to take you anywhere and small enough to make sure you get there.

Benefits:

Flexible working environment

Paid volunteer leave for those who wish to volunteer their services to a community organisation – 3 days per annum

Reward and Recognition Program to celebrate outstanding achievements of our people through a number of different delivery methods

Employee discounts with a range of partners

Up to 14 weeks of paid parental leave for primary care givers and 2 weeks of paid parental leave for secondary care givers

Unparalleled opportunities to advance and accelerate your career

Attractive options to purchase Brambles shares

Our team boasts a friendly and fun culture that celebrates successes, with award winning engagement and enablement, and results achieved through collective intelligence, collaboration, and teamwork.

With a highly inclusive workplace rich in diversity, Brambles celebrates the diversity of thought, backgrounds, style and working arrangements of our people to ensure that we reflect the communities and customers that we serve.

Join our team to be part of an international growth company with an advantaged and highly sustainable business model. You will be working for a company that is changing the way goods get to market. You will optimise 300,000 supply chains instead of just one. You will join an efficient and collaborative team who punches above its weight. You will be working for the good of humanity.

For your application to be considered, you will require full working rights in Australia. We are unable to offer sponsorship currently.

Senior Business Analyst - Omnichannel (Telephony)

The Opportunity

This role offers the chance to contribute to a major transformation program at a critical foundation phase, helping define and validate the future-state telephony and omnichannel capabilities across multiple regions. You will work closely with senior stakeholders and vendors to shape a modern, scalable platform that supports innovation and enhanced customer experiences.

The Role
As a Senior Business Analyst you will be responsible for leading requirements validation and analysis for the Omnichannel Telephony workstream.

Your other responsibilities will include:

Engaging with Sales, Service, Finance, Technology, and Facilities teams to validate and prioritise business requirements
Analysing current-state telephony platforms and defining future-state capability needs
Supporting vendor evaluation, solution assessment, and decision-making activities
Translating complex business needs into clear, structured requirements and documentation
Supporting delivery planning through detailed analysis and stakeholder alignment
Challenging legacy assumptions to support modern, fit-for-purpose solutions

About You

In order to be a successful applicant you will have strong experience working as a senior-level BA on telephony or omnichannel transformation initiatives.

You will also have:

Deep understanding of legacy PABX and cloud-based telephony platforms
Experience with contact centre technologies including IVR, call routing, and analytics
Exposure to platforms such as Genesys, AWS Connect, or NiCE (Genesys or AWS Connect preferred)
Experience supporting multi-country implementations and complex stakeholder environments
Salesforce Service Cloud experience (highly desirable)
Strong analytical, communication, and facilitation skills

Benefits

Long-term transformation program with strong extension prospects
Hybrid working environment with consistent team collaboration
Opportunity to influence foundational technology and service design decisions


Please note: We are receiving an extremely high volume of applications, please apply directly to the job advert and be patient while waiting for an update. Whilst we endeavour to respond to all enquiries, with current volumes it can be challenging - we're only human!

If you wish to apply via email please make sure you also apply directly - a lot of applications get phished, or sent to spam.

Please apply with current resume in Microsoft Word format only (.doc or .docx). helena.patterson@davidsonwp.com, JN -022026-42370. Want to know more about Davidson? Visit us at www.davidsonwp.com

About the role

We are seeking a talented PowerBI Developer to join the our team in our Perth office and abroad. As a PowerBI Developer, you will play a key role in helping our clients build and implement powerful data visualisation solutions that drive strategic business decisions and deliver Operational Excellence. This is a full-time position with flexible hours for 12 months.

What you'll be doing

Design and develop dynamic, feature-rich PowerBI dashboards and reports

Connect to a variety of data sources, transform and model data to create robust, scalable solutions

Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand requirements and translate them into effective data visualisations

Implement cutting-edge PowerBI features and functionality to enhance the user experience

Provide technical guidance and support to end-users, ensuring maximum adoption and utilisation of PowerBI solutions

Stay up-to-date with the latest PowerBI and Microsoft stack developments and best practices to continuously improve our offerings

What we're looking for

Proven experience as a PowerBI Developer or Business Intelligence Analyst with minimum 3+ years' experience

Excellent knowledge of the PowerBI suite of tools, including DAX, Power Query, Fabric and Power BI Desktop

Strong SQL skills for data modelling and ETL processes

Experience integrating PowerBI with a variety of data sources, such as SQL databases, Excel, and cloud-based platforms

Ability to translate business requirements into compelling and actionable data visualisations

Strong problem-solving and analytical skills, with a keen eye for detail

Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills

Experience with Power Automate, Power Apps and Python preferred but not essential

An engineering background with mining or manufacturing experience is highly preferred

Overview

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond. 

 As the Microsoft Continuous Improvement Program Manager (CIPM), you are responsible for identifying, leading and supporting strategic initiatives to improve operational performance across the organization. This role plays a key part in embedding a culture of continuous improvement by applying lean, six sigma and other performance enhancement methodologies. The ideal candidate has strong analytical capabilities, leadership skills and proven track record of driving impactful change. 

Responsibilities

We are seeking a data-driven, results-oriented Lean Sigma professional to lead and support process improvement initiatives across the organization. This role focuses on identifying inefficiencies, analyzing root causes, and implementing sustainable solutions using Lean and Six Sigma methodologies to reduce waste, improve quality, and enhance performance. 
 
Key Responsibilities: 

Lead and execute Lean Six Sigma projects to drive operational excellence. 

Analyze business processes and identify areas for cost savings, cycle time reduction, or quality improvement. 

Facilitate Kaizen events, value stream mapping, 5S audits, and process walkthroughs. 

Collaborate cross-functionally with teams in Operations, Quality, Engineering, Finance, IT, and HR to deliver measurable improvements. 

Collect and analyze data using statistical tools (e.g., Minitab, JMP, Excel). 

Develop and maintain process documentation, SOPs and control plans. 

Train and mentor Green Belts or Yellow Belts as needed. 

Track and report project progress and ROI to senior leadership. 

Qualifications

Required Qualifications 

Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Business, Operations, or a related field. 

Certified Lean Six Sigma Black Belt (ASQ, IASSC, or equivalent). 

Min. 7 years of relevant experience in process improvement or operational excellence roles. 

Proficiency in Lean tools (e.g., 5S, A3 Report, Kaizen Process, Value Stream Mapping, Standardized Work, Error Proofing, Takt Time/Cycle Time Analysis). 

Experience with statistical analysis tools (Minitab, SigmaXL, or equivalent). 

Strong problem-solving, facilitation, and project management skills. 

Excellent communication and stakeholder management capabilities.

Key KPIs: 

Number of projects completed 

Cost savings / ROI from improvement initiatives 

Defect reduction / quality improvement % 

Lead time or process cycle time improvement 

Employee engagement in CI activities 

Background Check Requirements: 

Ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role. These requirements include, but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: 

Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud background check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter.

Citizenship Verification: This position requires verification of Australian Citizenship to meet federal government security requirements.

NV1/2, PV Clearance Assessment: This position may require an enhanced background check conducted through the Australian Government Security Vetting Agency.

100% fully on-site role

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Category: Corporate Finance & Investment Banking (Banking & Financial Services)
Ad Text:
About the business

Our client is a well-established investment management group with a strong and growing footprint in land development and real assets. Their property arm focuses on the acquisition, feasibility, structuring and delivery of large-scale residential and mixed-use projects across Australia.

As their development pipeline continues to expand, they are seeking a highly analytical Investment Analyst to support investment and development decisions through best-in-class financial modelling and commercial analysis.

The opportunity

You will sit at the heart of the investment and development decision-making process, building and refining complex 3-way financial models that assess project feasibilities, returns, funding structures and risk scenarios.

Your work will directly influence which projects proceed, how they are structured, and how capital is deployed. This is not a reporting or month-end role – it is a commercial, forward-looking and decision-facing position. If you enjoy working in Excel, solving complex problems and seeing your analysis translate into real-world outcomes, this will be right up your alley.

Key responsibilities
Build, maintain and enhance detailed 3-way financial models (P&L, cash flow, balance sheet)
Develop land development feasibilities and investment models
Support acquisition underwriting and project evaluation
Perform sensitivity analysis, scenario modelling and stress testing
Analyse funding structures, returns and project economics
Assist with investment papers, board materials and decision packs
Continuously improve modelling frameworks and assumptions
Provide commercial insights to senior stakeholders
About you

You may come from a background such as:

Investment analysis
Corporate finance / transaction services / advisory
Development feasibilities or property analysis
Infrastructure or project finance
Valuations or modelling teams
You will ideally have:

Advanced Excel skills (essential)
Strong experience building 3-way models from scratch
A highly analytical and logical mindset
A degree in Finance, Economics, Mathematics, Engineering or similar
Strong attention to detail
The ability to translate numbers into clear commercial insights
Why this role?
High-impact, decision-facing position
Exposure to real capital deployment and development projects
Strong learning curve and career progression
Work closely with senior investment and development leaders

Company description:



Snowy Hydro is a dynamic, integrated energy business that has been providing on-demand, reliable energy to Australia for generations. Snowy Hydro owns and operates a powerful combination of generation assets, including the mighty Snowy Mountains Scheme, gas and diesel plants, and contracted wind and solar energy. We also provide electricity and gas to about 1.5 million retail customers through our retail brands Red Energy and Lumo Energy.




A full-time position exists for a Senior Strategic Analyst - Thermal to join the Strategy Team in the Planning and Performance stream.



Job description:



The Senior Strategic Analyst - Thermal will lead the ongoing performance and capability of Snowy Hydro's assets and operations and support strategic decision making to ensure we maintain our position and capability in a rapidly changing market. The role adds value by providing strategic perspective and analytical support for decision making processes associated with asset and operations strategy development, risk management and investment decision making. The Strategy Team supports key decision making inputs by linking technical engineering, operations, commercial and work execution strategies. This includes the development of requirements statements, asset life cycle models, and facility strategies to support the overarching Generation Business Plan. This includes extensive stakeholder engagement and front end communication across the business.




Snowy's Thermal portfolio includes 3 dual fuel Turbine Power Stations, 4 Diesel Stations with a capacity of ~1520MW, not including the 600MW Hunter Power Project. This role will be pivotal in informing the strategy for our assets and operations as we manage the challenges of a mixed portfolio of aging and new assets and changing market and operating context.




Key Responsibilities:




Lead the development of the Generation Business Plan to ensure we're planned and ready to deliver our corporate objectives.
Lead the development of Facility Strategies underpinned by life cycle and risk models to support capability, opportunities and investment plans.
Provide a key interface between technical engineering teams, strategy, planning and work execution teams to provide delivery assurance.
Help the business identity and realise value adding opportunities across our assets and operations.
Lead broader business decision making through ad-hoc analysis and decision making support.
Collaborating with others to ensure the Strategic team can extract the information needed for investment decision-making, life cycle costing, and setting long-term delivery strategies.




About the location:




This role offers flexibility in location, with the opportunity to be based in our Cooma, Sydney, or Melbourne office (with a strong preference for Cooma). Relocation support will be offered for anyone wanting to relocate to Cooma. You will be supporting and collaborating with multidisciplinary teams across the business to achieve shared strategic objectives.




About you:




We're looking for a self-starter with a proven industry background, a firm understanding of asset and risk management and an understanding of high criticality operating and commercial environments. You'll need to be able to blend the need to provide strategic thinking, leading analysis, stakeholder engagement and communication. This is not a technical role however a strong understanding of electrical, mechanical and civil assets in heavy industries is integral.




The person we are looking for should have the following capabilities:




An accomplished professional with a background (10+ years is ideal) in asset and business strategy, particularly within dynamic sectors like utilities, heavy industries, or mining.
Experience with thermal generating plant, particularly in a peaking context is highly desirable.
A sound technical understanding of generation or similar heavy assets (engineering or trade background preferred)
A strong foundation in a business-related discipline (such as a tertiary qualification in commerce, engineering, or CA/CPA or equivalent).
A solid management reporting background alongside demonstrated analytical skills and proficiency in data manipulation.
Demonstrated leadership, excellent stakeholder engagement, and a collaborative approach.
Strong verbal and written communication skills are essential, you'll regularly be engaging with stakeholders from all parts of the business.
The ability to draw meaningful conclusions while working in the grey area.
Capable of working autonomously and meeting deadlines.




About our workforce:




Diversity and inclusion is important to us. Snowy Hydro has a culture of decency and inclusion, with a commitment to the health and wellbeing of our people and a supportive environment to ensure that everyone - regardless of background - feels included and can succeed. At Snowy Hydro, we recognise that we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each individual brings, and we believe in providing an environment that allows that uniqueness to thrive.




Snowy Hydro is proud to be an Equal Opportunity employer. We are committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provide accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for a role with Snowy Hydro and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an email with your request to the Snowy Hydro recruitment team at recruitment@snowyhydro.com.au




If this role sounds like you, apply now! Applications close Monday 2nd March.

Strategy Advisor role driving growth, M&A and market strategy across Downer's Energy & Utilities business. Flexible working, exposure to executive leadership and high-impact strategic initiatives. Can be based in Brisbane or Melbourne.


The opportunity

Downer's Energy & Utilities business is seeking a Strategy Advisor to play a pivotal role in shaping long-term growth and investment decisions across Australia and New Zealand.

Reporting to the General Manager - Strategy, this role sits at the heart of the business, partnering with senior leaders across Water, Energy Networks, Telecommunications, Power Transmission & Storage and Industrials. You will provide deep financial, commercial and market insight to support M&A activity, strategic planning and sector positioning in a complex, ASX-listed environment.

This is a high-impact role suited to someone who enjoys working closely with executives, influencing decisions, and delivering strategic outcomes that directly shape the future of the business.

What you'll do

Build financial models, valuations and conduct due diligence to support M&A and strategic investments
Analyse market, industry and competitor trends to identify growth opportunities and risks
Partner with EGMs, GMs and senior leaders to develop sector strategies and market factbooks
Prepare high-quality executive reports, presentations and board papers
Provide economic and sector insights to inform medium and long-term strategic planning

What we offer

Flexible and hybrid working arrangements
Competitive remuneration within a Tier 1 ASX-listed organisation
Exposure to executive leadership and high-profile strategic initiatives
Career development through Downer's leadership and capability programs (including THRIVE and EmpowHER)
Access to Perks@Downer - discounts across finance, travel, wellbeing and lifestyle
Strong internal mobility and progression opportunities within Energy & Utilities

What we're looking for

Strong financial modelling, valuation and commercial analysis capability
Experience in strategy, management consulting, M&A, investment banking or similar
Ability to translate complex data into clear, actionable insights for senior stakeholders
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
A proactive, self-driven approach with strong stakeholder engagement skills

Downer's Energy & Utilities business is an integrated trans-Tasman team delivering services that connect communities to essential infrastructure. ASIC's Data, Analytics and AI Group is seeking a dynamic, highly skilled and experienced data professional to join its high‑performing team and provide expert guidance, leadership and uplift across ASIC's business registries and Registry Connect Program.

 

Sydney, Melbourne, Traralgon, Canberra and Brisbane locations available
24 Month Fixed Term Position
Salary from $168,164 to $181,284 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications will close at 11:59pm AEDT, Monday 9 February 2026

 

The team 

The Registry Connect Data team provides expert advice and support to ASIC's Registry Connect Program, ensuring that all deliverables are consistent, compliant with enterprise policies and aligned with industry best practice.

 

The role

The Data Solution Analyst will support the teams responsible for driving product development and the delivery of registry and regulatory outcomes. In this role, you will ensure that data governance, capabilities and best‑practice data management are effectively embedded into requirements and delivery. You will also help shape deliverables so they leverage modern data techniques, technologies and solutions to achieve high‑quality, sustainable outcomes.

 

More specifically, you will: 

Provide specialist data expertise to a team of product owners across the program, supporting the uplift and modernisation of ASIC's registers, user channels and interfaces. This includes ensuring that data capture, data governance requirements and contemporary data capabilities are fully considered, accurately reflected in solution design and effectively leveraged to deliver high‑quality, future‑ready outcomes.
Understand and advocate for user needs, ensuring that products are designed with a strong focus on consumer experience and high data quality.
Provide strategic, technical and professional advice on data considerations within user experience, user interface and accessibility design.
Ensure that all Registry Connect services are delivered in full compliance with ASIC's relevant organisational data governance standards and policies.

 

About you

The ideal candidate is an experienced and forward‑thinking data professional who combines strong analytical capability with a deep understanding of modern data practices. They will excel at translating business needs into well‑defined technical requirements and will work confidently with product owners, delivery teams and stakeholders to embed data governance, data quality and contemporary data solutions into program outcomes. They will also bring excellent communication skills, a collaborative mindset and strong attention to detail, along with the ability to solve problems creatively, navigate complexity and drive uplift across data processes, tools and capabilities.

 

In addition, you will have:

Demonstrated ability to understand business challenges, identify opportunities and translate these into well‑defined, clearly documented requirements.
Proven ability to build and maintain strong, collaborative relationships with key stakeholders to enable effective delivery of outcomes.
Strong attention to detail, with the ability to solve problems creatively and persistently.
Previous experience in effectively translating the information needs of the business into technical requirements for IT and conveying technology constraints back to the business. This includes supporting the operationalisation of business process optimisation and innovation initiatives.
Significant demonstrated experience in balancing and clearly articulating the interplay between business strategy and IT strategy, business process design and workflow automation, business initiatives and technology initiatives, while supporting effective benefit realisation and high‑quality service delivery.
Excellent communication, presentation and documentation skills with the ability to engage effectively with both technical and non-technical audiences at all levels.

Benefits realisation and process redesign

Change impacting ~100 internal administrator roles

Are you ready to be part of an organisation that values expertise, passion and diversity? At CFS we know that the foundation of our success lies in our exceptional people. We believe in celebrating individuality, have a passion for high performance and creating an environment where you can unleash your full potential. Our people enable us to make a difference and deliver exceptional experiences to help our customers achieve financial freedom.



Your Team

The Senior Manager, Data and Risk Insights leads the design and delivery of reporting and analytics tools that provide timely, actionable insights to reduce organisational risk and strengthen governance. As part of the Risk Transformation team, this role partners with senior leaders and stakeholders across the organisation to influence strategic decisions, embed data-driven practices, and uplift compliance maturity through the effective use of data.

By leveraging advanced analytics and visualisation, the role supports risk transformation, fosters transparency, and drives continuous improvement to enable sustainable governance and better business outcomes.

This role reports into the Executive Director of Risk Transformation.


Your Responsibilities


Lead the development and delivery of risk insights and analytics, enabling proactive risk management and informed decision-making across the organisation.
Design and maintain robust risk reporting frameworks, ensuring data integrity, timeliness, and compliance with internal standards and regulatory requirements.

Transmax is seeking a Commercial Analyst to provide high-quality commercial insight, pricing analysis and deal assurance that supports profitable and sustainable growth. Sitting within the Customer & Product group, this hands-on role works across the full commercial lifecycle, partnering closely with sales, product, finance and legal teams to ensure pricing, commercial terms and financial assumptions are robust, compliant and aligned to margin and risk objectives. Your work will directly inform bid, renewal and investment decisions across the business.

You will play a lead role in structuring and pricing deals, developing fit-for-purpose pricing models that balance competitiveness with profitability. This includes building and testing deal scenarios, undertaking sensitivity analysis and establishing clear commercial guardrails. You’ll ensure key assumptions such as indexation, service levels, credits, liabilities and performance measures are clearly documented, well understood and consistently applied, supporting confidence in commercial decision-making.

A core focus of the role is high-quality financial modelling and analysis. You will develop cash flow models, NPV and IRR analysis, payback assessments and scenario modelling to support commercial proposals. You’ll also analyse unit economics, resource plans and utilisation impacts on margin, helping articulate clear ROI and value narratives for both internal stakeholders and customers.

Additionally, you will support strong commercial governance and in-life contract performance. This includes preparing deal review packs for approval forums, tracking approvals and exceptions, and working with Finance and Legal to identify and mitigate commercial risk. You will monitor contract performance across the portfolio, identify margin leakage and value-uplift opportunities, and contribute market and competitive insights to inform pricing strategy.

This is a role for a commercially astute analyst who wants their work to genuinely influence outcomes and help shape smarter, more sustainable decisions at Transmax.

You are a confident Learning & Capability professional with strong organisational development experience. You enjoy balancing strategy with hands-on delivery and are comfortable working within a close team environment and partnering with senior leaders to design and implement impactful OD and development solutions. You bring strong analytical capability, are comfortable working with data and psychometric tools, and have a genuine interest in shaping culture, leadership, and organisational performance. You thrive in a small, agile environment and are motivated by making a tangible, organisation-wide impact.

If you’re a Learning & Capability Specialist with strong organisational development skills open to new opportunities and are keen to have a confidential career conversation, please contact Anna Luff at aluff@thenextstep.com.au or 0433 411 518, quoting reference number 4002933.

Category:
Programme & Project Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
The role:

The Principal Benefits Analyst role supports the Manager, Benefits Management to provide a dedicated benefits and value management service to a complex ICT program, governed, managed and reported within the Delivery Services Branch, eHealth Queensland. It will review existing business cases and benefits information. This role will review and finalise benefit artefacts, facilitate agreement with stakeholders, maintain the benefit register and proactively track and report their progress and realisation.

Is this opportunity for you?

To be successful in this role, you must have:

Demonstrated experience leading and managing benefits management activities within IM/ICT clinical programs and projects, preferably within the public healthcare industry.
Demonstrate stakeholder engagement and consultation experience working effectively in multi-disciplinary including clinical teams, building productive relationships with team members and stakeholders, and mentoring program and project managers within the Delivery Services Branch.
Proven skills in consultation, facilitation, and both written and oral communication, tailored for use in a complex ICT project environment.
Proven expertise in SharePoint and Power BI, including experience developing dynamic portfolio dashboards to support decision-making.
Applied knowledge of APMG-International's Managing Benefits methodology at practitioner level, with experience in identifying, quantifying, analysing, planning, tracking, realising, and optimising benefits, would be highly desirable.

About eHealth Queensland:

eHealth Queensland is one of the largest Information and Communication Technology operations in the state. It is responsible for ensuring the smooth operation of information systems and technologies so that Queensland Health employees and health providers have access to information that supports the delivery of health care.

Benefits of working with eHealth Queensland:

By joining eHealth Queensland, you will work within a fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment where every employee plays a critical role in our ongoing success. 

You will enjoy a variety of benefits, including:

Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading
Flexible working arrangements
Diverse work culture
Career training and development

To apply for this exciting opportunity, please provide the following information in your application:

Your current CV or resume
A short statement (maximum 2 pages) on how your experience, abilities, knowledge, and personal qualities are relevant for the role, taking into account the key responsibilities and attributes noted in the ‘How you will be assessed?' section of the Role Description.

About Airwallex


Airwallex is the only unified payments and financial platform for global businesses. Powered by our unique combination of proprietary infrastructure and software, we empower over 200,000 businesses worldwide – including Brex, Rippling, Navan, Qantas, SHEIN and many more – with fully integrated solutions to manage everything from business accounts, payments, spend management and treasury, to embedded finance at a global scale.

Proudly founded in Melbourne, we have a team of over 2,000 of the brightest and most innovative people in tech across 26 offices around the globe. Valued at US$8 billion and backed by world-leading investors including T. Rowe Price, Visa, Mastercard, Robinhood Ventures, Sequoia, Salesforce Ventures, DST Global, and Lone Pine Capital, Airwallex is leading the charge in building the global payments and financial platform of the future. If you’re ready to do the most ambitious work of your career, join us.

Attributes We Value


We hire successful builders with founder-like energy who want real impact, accelerated learning, and true ownership. You bring strong role-related expertise and sharp thinking, and you’re motivated by our mission and operating principles. You move fast with good judgment, dig deep with curiosity, and make decisions from first principles, balancing speed and rigor.

You’re humble and collaborative; turn zero‑to‑one ideas into real products, and you “get stuff done” end-to-end. You use AI to work smarter and solve problems faster. Here, you’ll tackle complex, high‑visibility problems with exceptional teammates and grow your career as we build the future of global banking. If that sounds like you, let’s build what’s next.

About the team


The Strategic Data Science team provides Airwallex’s Leadership with the data, tooling, and insights needed to amplify Airwallex’s rapid growth. We partner across the entire business, giving us an overarching view and opinion on what Airwallex should prioritize. Our expertise spans the full data stack, and we use it to tackle complex data problems that will shape the future of global fintech. The team is growing quickly, and currently resides in the US, China, and Singapore. Learn more about the data science team in this blog.

This role is based in Melbourne.

Responsibilities:


Be the go-to data partner for regional executives

Partner with Sales, Marketing, Finance, Data Engineering, and Product to align metric definitions/dimensions and data sources across the business

Leverage AI to generate insights and improve business and team efficiency

Support Airwallex’s forecasting efforts by applying advanced statistical methods

Scope and build data products. In some cases MVPs, and in others, fully fleshed out solutions

Foster an environment grounded in technical excellence, clear communication, and proactive critical thinking

Who you are


We’re looking for people who meet the minimum qualifications for this role. The preferred qualifications are great to have, but are not mandatory.

Minimum qualifications:


5+ years industry experience and a degree in a quantitative field (e.g. Statistics, Engineering, Sciences, Computer Science, Economics)

Excellent communication skills, ideally with a proven track record of working directly with executive-level stakeholders to influence strategy

Expertise in forecasting

Expertise in data querying languages (e.g. SQL) and scripting languages (e.g. Python, R)

Experience with data architecture technologies such as Airflow, Databricks, and dbt

Preferred qualifications:


Experience in technology, financial services and/or a high growth environment

Experience with Excel and Finance systems (e.g. Oracle)

#melbourne

All official communication will come from an @airwallex.com email address. Please apply only through careers.airwallex.com or our official LinkedIn page.

Search firms/recruiters submitting resumes to Airwallex on an unsolicited basis shall be deemed to accept this condition, regardless of any other provision to the contrary.

Equal opportunity


Airwallex is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We value diversity and anyone seeking employment at Airwallex is considered based on merit, qualifications, competence and talent. We don’t regard color, religion, race, national origin, sexual orientation, ancestry, citizenship, sex, marital or family status, disability, gender, or any other legally protected status when making our hiring decisions. Drive impact by reducing Alinta’s risks from growing cyber threats in energy
Lead and influence cyber uplift across tech and security teams
Attractive hybrid work model | Energy Discounts | Career Growth Opportunities

Alinta Energy is one of Australia’s biggest energy retailers, generators and developers with over 1.1 million customers. Australia’s energy system is undergoing the biggest transformation in its history and we’re right there with it. We’re investing in and developing large-scale renewables and storage projects as part of our ongoing effort to provide our customers with reliable, affordable and sustainable energy.

We understand that flexibility matters when considering your next role. Let us know your requirements, and we’ll carefully consider how we might accommodate them.

Ready to make a real impact?

Step into a key role within our Cyber Security Program Management team, where you’ll help drive the reduction of Alinta’s most critical cyber risks. Based in either Melbourne or Adelaide, you’ll engage closely with Technology, Risk, Security Operations and Compliance to understand the factors behind our cyber risks and guide the uplift required to resolve them. In this role, you’ll help shape, deliver and oversee a portfolio of security initiatives, ensuring uplift work stays on track and contributes to long-term improvement across our cyber landscape. It’s a proactive, high-impact position where you’ll collaborate with engaged stakeholders and influence meaningful security outcomes. As part of Alinta’s strong commitment to flexibility, we welcome both full-time and part-time applicants, supporting you to balance work with what matters most.

Why you’ll love working here

At Alinta Energy, we’re taking real action to deliver reliable and sustainable energy for Australia — and that practical approach runs through everything we do. You’ll get clear direction, genuine flexibility, and the support you need to grow, all while working on projects that make a lasting difference. We’re big enough to create impact, but small enough that your ideas and effort will always be seen.

There are plenty of other great benefits of working for Alinta Energy, including flexible working, energy discounts, an Employee Assistance Program (EAP), a paid volunteer day each year, fully stocked kitchens, and lots more.

What you'll do

Lead and support the delivery, oversight and reporting of cyber risk-reduction initiatives across the business.
Develop program documentation, project briefs, and portfolio planning that aligns with our Cyber Security Program Strategy and AESCSF practices.
Work closely with technology teams to uplift deficient controls, support change adoption, and embed standard security patterns within projects.
Monitor project milestones, budgets, change management effectiveness and the adoption of security outcomes by control owners.
Prepare clear program updates and reporting for senior stakeholders, including the GM Security & Risk and the Audit & Risk Committee (ARC).

Your experience

Strong background in cybersecurity, ideally across risk, governance, compliance, or security operations, with hands-on experience implementing or uplifting security controls.
Experience delivering or overseeing technology or cyber-related projects or programs, with the ability to influence stakeholders and guide outcomes.
A solid understanding of cloud security (Azure/AWS), network security fundamentals, antimalware solutions, and encryption practices.
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to translate complex technical issues for non-technical audiences and build strong stakeholder relationships.
Strong analytical thinking and problem-solving skills, with the ability to operate calmly and effectively in dynamic, high-pressure environments.

Please note this role requires full working rights within Australia.

Like what you’re seeing?

If you like the sound of this, and you’ve got experience in a similar role, we’d love to talk to you. Come and discover better together with Alinta Energy.

We are a 2026 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant.

If your application progresses, we will need to complete background and pre-employment checks, such as immigration checks, reference checks, criminal background checks, qualification checks, and additional checks for roles related to finance.

Our Diversity Commitment

Alinta Energy offers a truly diverse, safe and supportive work environment. As an equal opportunity employer, Alinta Energy encourages applications from any qualified person, including First Nations Australians, members of the LGBTQIA+ community, people of all ages and people living with a disability. We are also proud to be a WORK180 Endorsed Employer and we are committed to advancing women’s careers.

We look forward to hearing from you.

Click ‘Apply’ to submit your application.

Job Title: Enterprise Product Strategy & Business Operations, Senior Manager
Ad Text:
Working at Atlassian

Atlassians can choose where they work – whether in an office, from home, or a combination of the two. That way, Atlassians have more control over supporting their family, personal goals, and other priorities. We can hire people in any country where we have a legal entity.

Atlassian is seeking a Senior Manager of Strategy and Business Operations who will partner directly with leaders in our Enterprise Foundations organization. Enterprise Foundations aims to provide a robust and reliable cloud platform that meets the complex needs of enterprise customers, facilitating their transition to and success in the cloud environment.

If you are looking to make a global impact, partner with world-class talent, and take your career to the next level, we encourage you to join us on this exciting journey. You are a good fit if you are driven, highly organised, analytical and have strong business acumen.

At Atlassian, the Strategy & Business Operations team is a high impact team that works closely with business leaders across the company. Our team takes a lead role in driving strategy, growth, and business operations. You’ll own projects from inception to execution and delivery, ensuring that the strategies you develop are creative and offer high-quality and impactful recommendations to business partners.

In this role, you'll get to:

Partner directly with product, go-to-market, analytics and finance teams to help prioritize product roadmaps, deliver strategic recommendations and analyses, and

Develop product strategies that drive growth for the business, and drive strategic and data-driven decision-making to inform business decisions through thorough financial & analytical modeling, research and insights

Be a self-starter and drive work from idea to analysis, recommendation and, at times, to implementation

Define appropriate goals/OKRs to track progress against strategic objectives

Keep a tight pulse on business performance and reporting, including "quarterbacking" a cross-functional team to diagnose problems when they occur

On your first day, we'll expect you to have:

Have 8+ years experience in high growth software / tech industry in BizOps and / or consulting, investment banking roles

Contribute to executive level decision making, including articulately presenting and debating recommendations

Enjoy working with numbers and both understand the details and see / communicate the bigger picture

Break down complex problems and take a hypothesis-driven approach to problem solving

Be comfortable with ambiguity and bring a structured approach to decision-making

Proficiency in financial modelling and building revenue and cost drivers

Be intellectually curious and genuinely excited about technology

It's great, but not required of you to have:


Industry experience in SaaS or platform business models

Experience using SQL for analysis

Knowledge of BI tools and technologies (e.g. Tableau)

Atlassian offers a wide range of perks and benefits designed to support you, your family and to help you engage with your local community. Our offerings include health and wellbeing resources, paid volunteer days, and so much more. To learn more, visit go.atlassian.com/perksandbenefits.

About Atlassian

At Atlassian, we're motivated by a common goal: to unleash the potential of every team. Our software products help teams all over the planet and our solutions are designed for all types of work. Team collaboration through our tools makes what may be impossible alone, possible together.

We believe that the unique contributions of all Atlassians create our success. To ensure that our products and culture continue to incorporate everyone's perspectives and experience, we never discriminate based on race, religion, national origin, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, or marital, veteran, or disability status. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.

To provide you the best experience, we can support with accommodations or adjustments at any stage of the recruitment process. Simply inform our Recruitment team during your conversation with them.

To learn more about our culture and hiring process, visit go.atlassian.com/crh.
